The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 March is 244,414 (28,170.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 March, there were 8,050 new confirmed cases (927.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 March, there were 4,746 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 70% (3,304 extra cases).
